#31419
Norse Stronghold Entrance~
   There is light coming from flickering torches that line the walls further
down the wide passageway.  The walls here are made of thick wooden breams
running vertically and large stones mortared between them.  The beams are met
at their peaks with similarly sized beams that lay horizontally on the
ceiling.  Footsteps echo on the hard-packed dirt floor.  The passage continues
to the south where the light from the torches beckon.  
~
