#31421
Well-lit Passage~
   Several torches line the passageway here and it is brightly lit as a
result.  The wall to the south is the same stone and wooden beam, but to the
north a symbol has been etched into a very large square stone that has been
set into the wall.  Three large candles are lit and sit on the dirt packed floor beneath
this symbol, drawing pointed attention to the importance this symbol holds.  
The passage continues to the east where it appears to bend north ahead.  
~
