E
symbol wall etch~
The etched symbol was crafted with care by patient hands.  The linework is
smooth and made by someone experienced in this kind of work.  The symbol
consists of three thick triangles that interweave at the center.  Around these
triangles, runes are etched in into a border.  The symbol is called the
Valknut and honors slain warriors that Odin welcomes into Valhalla.  The nine
points of the triangles symbolizes the Nine Worlds.  
~
S
#31422
Bend in the Passage~
   This bend marks the end of the entrance passage and the beginning of the
living quarters of the stronghold.  A large iron chandelier of candles lights
the passage here in flickering bright light.  The mortared stone and wooden
beam walls can be seen easier here and the craftsmanship is apparent.  They
seem strong enough to withstand an assault of nature or man.  The passage
opens up to the north.  
~
