#31425
The Dvergar's Forge~
   Heat from the forge in the northwestern corner of the room makes the air
feel oppressive.  The forge was made when this room was constructed and the
smoke from the forge is led out by a vent connected to he northwestern corner
of the ceiling.  The forge itself is casted from extremely thick steel and
burns brightly casting an orange glow on everything in the room.  An anvil the
size of an elephants head sits in front of the forge and a blacksmith hammer
is mounted on the northern wall in the center.  A halved barrel sits at the
eastern wall containing water for extinguishing and metal-work.  A table at
the southern wall contains various tools used for shaping and hammering the
metals.  A single large lantern hangs from the tall ceiling from a beam
assisting the forge in lighting the room.  
~
