#31489
A dimly lit tunnel~
   This tunnel was dug carefully in the soil and braced with thick wooden
beams, similar to the stronghold's structure.  A torch on the a northern beam
casts dim light for guidance.  An earthy smell permeates the moist air.  If it
weren't for the torch on the northern beam, the tunnel would be pitch black.
